The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Pharma major Lupin Ltd has posted a 32 per cent jump in net profit at Rs 408.2 crore for the year ended March 2008 compared with Rs 308.6 crore during the same period last year. Its total income surged 34 per cent to Rs 2,773 crore from Rs 2,071.7 crore a year ago. Lupin chairman D.B. Gupta said the company would invest Rs 300 crore for expansion and acquisition in the current year. Export revenues were at Rs 1,529.2 crore, a rise of 52 per cent.                            
	 Mobile chip maker Qualcomm is in talks with vendors and original equipment manufacturers (OEM) to launch smartphones, priced at Rs 10,000, in the country by next year. Qualcomm has OEM partners such as ZTE, Huawei, LG, Samsung and HTC.                             
	 Ford India has commenced production of diesel engines at its Maramalai Nagar plant in Chennai for use in mid-sized cars  the Fiesta and the Fusion. The $26-million unit has a production capacity of 50,000 diesel engines and 10,000 petrol annually.                            
	 Israel Aerospace Industries and Tata Sons have signed a framework agreement for cooperation in the development, manufacturing and marketing of defence and aerospace products such as missiles, UAVs, radars, electronic warfare systems and homeland security systems in India.                             
	 Ramsarup Industries has received the clean development mechanism clearance from UNFCCC for its 20 mega watt WHRB power project at Kharagpur. The project will reduce the emission of 114,996 million tonnes of carbon dioxide in the atmosphere.                             
	 Hyderabad based Institute of Life Sciences (ILS), a joint venture of the Andhra Pradesh government, the University of Hyderabad and Dr Reddys Laboratories, has entered into a research collaboration agreement with Melbourne-based Baker Heart Research Institute. According to the agreement, the parties will work on identifying therapeutic molecules in diabetes and obesity.                             
	 Xylys has launched Swiss-made chronograph watch Magnum Indigo. This time wear combines the watch-making expertise of Swiss with international styling.                             
	 Tata Indicom has launched online store www.ichoose.com to help prepaid customers buy recharge vouchers online. The facility is accessible in 400 cities across the country.                            
	 Phoenix Yule Ltd has received the first prize in Environment Excellence Awards 2007 organised at the Oberoi Grand, Calcutta.                                                                                                                                      ADVERTISEMENT                   
